# Chapter 3 — Classes

## Biggest truth

`class` is mostly prettier syntax.

Under the hood:

```
class
      ↓
prototype system
```

---

## Constructor

Runs only with `new`.

```
new User("Shiva")
        ↓
constructor()
```

---

## Where everything lives

| Thing | Lives |
|------|------|
| Fields | Instance |
| Methods | Prototype |
| Static | Constructor |
| Private | Declaring class only |

Memorize this table.

---

## this

Inside instance methods:

```
this === current instance
```

Inside static methods:

```
this === constructor/class
```

---

## Public fields

```
class User{
    name=""
}
```

Mental model:

```
constructor(){
    this.name=""
}
```

---

## Arrow functions inside class

Avoid:

```
login = ()=>{}
```

Why?

Every instance creates a brand new function.

Prefer:

```
login(){}
```

One function.
Shared through prototype.

---

## extends

Creates relationships.

Not copies.

```
Admin
   │
   ▼
User
```

---

## super

Constructor:

```
super(...)
```

Must happen before `this`.

Methods:

```
super.login()
```

Runs parent implementation.

---

## Overriding

Child can replace parent behavior.

Use:

```
super.method()
```

when parent behavior is still needed.

---

## instanceof

Checks the prototype chain.

```
admin instanceof User
```

True because User.prototype exists in the chain.

---

## Sharing, not Copying

The most important sentence from the whole chapter.

Methods stay exactly where they were created.

Instances borrow them.

They never receive copies.

---

## Static

Static belongs to the class.

```
User.company
```

Not:

```
user.company
```

Think:

Company belongs to the organization.

Name belongs to the employee.

---

## Private

```
#password
```

Only code written inside that declaring class can access it.

Even subclasses cannot.

---

## Brand check

```
#password in obj
```

Safe boolean check.

No exception.

---

## Private static gotcha

Inside inherited static methods:

Prefer

```
User.#count
```

instead of

```
this.#count
```

---

# Mental Models

### Prototype
A family tree.

### Instance
A person.

### Prototype
The shared DNA.

### Static
The company's information.

### Instance
The employee's information.

### Private
A safe whose key only one class owns.

